The contractors are graduates from the Youth Brigade Programme, which provides construction skills training and work placement opportunities. CAPE TOWN Over 1,500 new affordable housing units have been built in Mfuleni by contractors trying to grow their own businesses.The 20 contractors are graduates from the Western Cape Human Settlements' Youth Brigade Programme, which provides construction skills training and work placement opportunities.100 emerging contractors have been trained in the programme so far.Provincial Human Settlements MEC Bonginkosi Madikizela on Friday celebrated the group of young people who have been working on the department's R246 million Bardale housing project. That will go a long way in addressing the plight of those young people. We were celebrating the work that was done by emerging contractors. They have done sterling work, producing quality houses that are bigger within the subsidy. 